# 📧 Email Spam Detection using Machine Learning

## Project Overview

This project implements an **Email Spam Detection System** using **Machine Learning** and **Natural Language Processing (NLP)** techniques. The objective is to classify email or SMS messages as **Spam** or **Ham (Not Spam)** based on their textual content.

The model was trained using the **Multinomial Naive Bayes** algorithm with **TF-IDF Vectorization**, enabling fast and accurate spam classification.

---

# Problem Statement

Email spam is one of the most common cybersecurity and communication challenges. Spam messages often contain advertisements, phishing links, scams, or malicious content that can negatively impact users.

The objective of this project is to:

* Automatically classify messages as Spam or Ham.
* Reduce manual effort in identifying spam emails.
* Build a machine learning model capable of making real-time predictions.
* Develop a foundation for an intelligent email filtering system.

---

