# Performance Analysis

## Accuracy

**96.80%**

The model correctly classified nearly **97 out of every 100** messages.

---

## Precision

**100.00%**

Whenever the model predicts **Spam**, the prediction is correct.

False Positives = **0**

This means legitimate emails were never incorrectly classified as spam on the test set.

---

## Recall

**74.22%**

The model correctly identified approximately **74%** of all spam messages.

About **26%** of spam emails were missed and classified as ham.

---

## F1 Score

**85.20%**

The F1-score balances precision and recall.

An F1-score above **85%** demonstrates strong overall classification performance despite the class imbalance.

