# Conclusion

This project successfully demonstrates the practical application of **Machine Learning** and **Natural Language Processing** for email spam detection. By combining TF-IDF Vectorization with the Multinomial Naive Bayes algorithm, the model achieved an **accuracy of 96.80%**, **100% precision**, and an **F1-score of 85.20%**. The system effectively distinguishes spam from legitimate messages while ensuring that genuine emails are not incorrectly flagged. This project serves as a strong foundation for building intelligent email filtering systems and can be further enhanced using advanced NLP models and deep learning techniques.
